South African Stocks Rise Most in a Week as Commodities Advance

-- B y   S i k o n a t h i   M a n t s h a n t s h a
-- 
2011-06-07T10:25:19Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-07/south-african-stocks-rise-most-in-a-week-as-commodities-advance.html
South African shares gained the most
in a week, led by mining companies  BHP Billiton Plc (BIL)  and  Anglo
American Plc (AGL) , as metals prices increased.  The FTSE/JSE Africa All Share Index rose for a second day,
increasing 180.77, or 0.6 percent to 31,758.80 by 11:57 a.m. in
Johannesburg. BHP Billiton Plc, the worldâ€™s largest mining
company, advanced the most since May 27, gaining 1.2 percent to
259.29 rand while diversified miner  Anglo American Plc (AAL)  increased
0.9 percent to 331.10 rand, a second day of advances.  Lead, nickel, tin and zinc climbed on the London Metal
Exchange.  To contact the reporter on this story:
